{#
  Day-grouped chronological log for the current history period, newest day
  first. Each entry row has a stable .entry-row wrapper so the edit-in-place
  flow can swap it via hx-target="closest .entry-row" / hx-swap="outerHTML".

  The pencil edit button is shown only when history.is_owner is true.

  The comment toggle + #comment-slot-{{ entry.id }} mirrors the affordance
  formerly in web/activity_detail.html.jinja2's standalone Comments section
  (since folded into this shared log). It renders only when there's
  something to show (an existing count, or the viewer can add one) AND the
  activity has a public URL — history.username/history.slug are None for a
  guest-owned activity, which has no `/@{username}/{slug}` route to hit.

  An anonymous (no session) visitor on an otherwise-readable activity has
  history.can_comment=False (can_comment_on_entry requires a session) AND no
  existing comment_count, so neither branch above would render anything —
  that's the silently-missing-composer gap this build fixes. When
  history.login_redirect_url is set (only ever built on the already-
  capability-cleared read-only path; see app/routes/public.py and
  app/routes/web.py::activity_history), an entry with zero comments shows a
  "log in to comment" link to it instead. An entry that already has
  comments still shows the normal read-only toggle (reading stays open to
  anonymous visitors; only posting is gated).

  Context:
    history        — history context (history.log: [{"day": "YYYY-MM-DD", "entries": [...]}]);
                     history.is_owner, history.can_comment, history.username,
                     history.slug, history.login_redirect_url are passed
                     straight through from app.routes.web._build_history_context.
    activity_id   int    — owning activity (needed for edit-route URLs)

  Per-entry markup lives in the shared components/_entry_row.html.jinja2
  macro (also used by day_entries.html.jinja2 and the edit/cancel-edit
  swap-back fragment) so all three render the identical row shape.
#}
{% from "components/_entry_row.html.jinja2" import entry_row %}

<div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
    {% if not history.log %}
        <p class="text-caption text-text-muted">{{ strings.HISTORY_LOG_EMPTY }}</p>
    {% else %}
        <ul class="divide-y divide-border">
            {% for day_group in history.log %}
                {% for entry in day_group.entries %}
                    {{ entry_row(
                        entry,
                        activity_id,
                        is_owner=history.is_owner,
                        can_comment=history.can_comment,
                        username=history.username,
                        slug=history.slug,
                        expand_comment_entry_id=history.expand_comment_entry_id,
                        login_redirect_url=history.login_redirect_url,
                    ) }}
                {% endfor %}
            {% endfor %}
        </ul>
    {% endif %}
</div>
